#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.169"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.169:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.169:0.2"
msgid "17. Paṭipadāvagga "
msgstr "17. Practice "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: kilesaparinibbānasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.169:0.3"
msgid "169. Sasaṅkhārasutta "
msgstr "169. Extra Effort "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.169:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.169:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol><li>
msgctxt "an4.169:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti. "
msgstr "One person becomes fully extinguished in the present life by making extra effort. "

#. HTML: </li><li>
msgctxt "an4.169:1.4"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kāyassa bhedā sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti. "
msgstr "One person becomes fully extinguished when the body breaks up by making extra effort. "

#. HTML: </li><li>
msgctxt "an4.169:1.5"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti. "
msgstr "One person becomes fully extinguished in the present life without making extra effort. "

#. HTML: </li><li>
msgctxt "an4.169:1.6"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kāyassa bhedā asaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti. "
msgstr "One person becomes fully extinguished when the body breaks up without making extra effort. "

#. HTML: </li></ol><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.156, sc2
msgctxt "an4.169:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a person become fully extinguished in the present life by making extra effort? "

msgctxt "an4.169:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu asubhānupassī kāye viharati, āhāre paṭikūlasaññī, sabbaloke anabhiratisaññī, sabbasaṅkhāresu aniccānupassī. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates observing the ugliness of the body, perceives the repulsiveness of food, perceives dissatisfaction with the whole world, observes the impermanence of all conditions, "

msgctxt "an4.169:2.3"
msgid "Maraṇasaññā kho panassa ajjhattaṃ sūpaṭṭhitā hoti. "
msgstr "and has well established the perception of their own death. "

msgctxt "an4.169:2.4"
msgid "So imāni pañca sekhabalāni upanissāya viharati—"
msgstr "They rely on these five powers of a trainee: "

msgctxt "an4.169:2.5"
msgid "saddhābalaṃ, hiribalaṃ, ottappabalaṃ, vīriyabalaṃ, paññābalaṃ. "
msgstr "faith, conscience, prudence, energy, and wisdom. "

msgctxt "an4.169:2.6"
msgid "Tassimāni pañcindriyāni adhimattāni pātubhavanti—"
msgstr "And they have these five faculties strongly: "

msgctxt "an4.169:2.7"
msgid "saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom. "

msgctxt "an4.169:2.8"
msgid "So imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ adhimattattā diṭṭheva dhamme sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti. "
msgstr "Because of the strength of the five faculties, they become fully extinguished in the present life by making extra effort. "

msgctxt "an4.169:2.9"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo diṭṭheva dhamme sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a person becomes fully extinguished in the present life by making extra effort. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.169:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo kāyassa bhedā sasaṅkhāraparinibbāyī hoti? "
msgstr "How does a person become fully extinguished when the body breaks up by making extra effort? "

